Class RingBuffer<T extends @Nullable Object>

java.lang.Object
com.dua3.utility.lang.RingBuffer<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the element type
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, SequencedCollection<T>
public class RingBuffer<T extends @Nullable Object> extends Object implements SequencedCollection<T>
A ring buffer implementation. This class behaves much like @see ArrayList, but with a fixed maximum size.

The collection grows when new elements are added until the capacity is reached. If even more items are added, the oldest element is removed and the new element appended to the collection. Adding is O(1).

      public List<T> subList(int fromIndex, int toIndex)
      Returns a view of the portion of this buffer between the specified fromIndex, inclusive, and toIndex, exclusive. (If fromIndex and toIndex are equal, the returned list is empty.) The returned list is backed by this buffer.
      Parameters:
      fromIndex - low endpoint (inclusive) of the subList
      toIndex - high endpoint (exclusive) of the subList
      Returns:
      a view of the specified range within this list
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - for an illegal endpoint index value (fromIndex < 0 || toIndex > size || fromIndex > toIndex)
